<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-040-176 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 374 097</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Oct 3 1991 n1775* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM to aid US colleges in total quality. (promoting qualitycontrol education)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Public relations).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Public RelationsDonationColleges and UniversitiesQuality control.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM TO AID US COLLEGES IN TOTAL QUALITYandM;IBM Corp has unveiled a major new programme in the US intended to helpuniversities to implement total quality management concepts in teaching,research and operations.andP;  The multi-million dollar programme will providefunding, equipment, technical support and partnerships to implement totalquality management concepts in core courses in business, engineering,statistics and related areas; conduct research on successful such programmesand programme components already implemented; and implement total qualitymanagement concepts in the operations of the university itself.andP;  ChairmanJohn Akers commented that the company is &quot;launching this competition amonguniversities to encourage education, research and self-betterment in totalquality management concepts&quot; - and it is no doubt no coincidence that Akersis this year's chairman of National Quality Month, October 1991.andP;  The new IBMprogramme is open to all universities and colleges in the US and is intendedto promote interdisciplinary research and education on quality and help themrun themselves.andO;</TEXT></DOC>